{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/simple-click/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"3a5777c3-6ad7-53ec-8083-caff9e74285c","html":"<p><img src=\"../../../2020-02-02%2009-47-14_Start.png\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../../2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"../../../static/flex-fcf17f1150c7ef3318be35f75bcbe73e.png\"></p>\n<p>cli tools are super handy and easy to add to your python libraries to supercharge them. Even if your library is not a cli tool there are a number of things that a cli can do to your library.</p>\n<h1>Example Ideas</h1>\n<p>Things a cli can do to enhance your library.</p>\n<p>üÜö print version\nüï∂ print readme\nüìù print changelog<br>\nüìÉ print config<br>\n‚úè change config<br>\nüë©‚Äçüéì run a tutorial<br>\nüèó scaffold a project with cookiecutter</p>\n<h1>üñ± <a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a></h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a> is the most popular python cli tool framework for python. There are others, some old, some new comers that make take the crown. For now <a href=\"https://click.palletsprojects.com/\">Click</a> is the gold standard if you want to make a powerful cli quickly. If you are dependency conscious and dont need a lot of tooling, use <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/argparse.html\">argparse</a>.</p>\n<h1>Project Structure</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">.\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ setup.py\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ simple_click\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cli.py\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ __init__.py</code></pre></div>\n<h1>‚ùØ cli.py</h1>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"># simple_click/cli.py\nimport click\n\n__version__ = &quot;1.0.0&quot;\n\n@click.group()\ndef cli():\n   pass\n\n@cli.command()\ndef version():\n    &quot;&quot;&quot;prints project version&quot;&quot;&quot;\n    click.echo(__version__)\n\n\nif __name__ == &#39;__main__&#39;:\n    cli()</code></pre></div>\n<h1>‚ú® <strong>init</strong>.py</h1>\n<p>For our simple<em>click library <code class=\"language-text\">__init__.py__</code> can be left empty. It is here purely to signify that simple</em>click is a library. It is likely that you will import other modules here that need to reside at the top level of your library api, your cli does not need to be at the top of of your api.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"># __init__.py</code></pre></div>\n<h1>üö™ Entry Points</h1>\n<p>Entry points are the magic that make python cli tools available as their own command without having python before it or the file extension.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"># setup.py\n\nfrom setuptools import setup, find_packages\n\n# this is the ü•© meat of this snippet\n# simple_click is the command name\n# = simple_click is the library name\n# .cli is the cli.py file\n# :cli is the cli function\n#\n# the second item is a shorthand alias to the main command\n\nentry_points = [\n   &quot;simple_click = simple_click.cli:cli&quot;,\n   &quot;scli         = simple_click.cli:cli&quot;,\n]\n\n\nsetup(\n    name=&#39;simple_click&#39;,\n    version=&#39;1.0.0&#39;,\n    url=&#39;https://github.com/mypackage.git&#39;,\n    packages=find_packages(),\n    entry_points={&quot;console_scripts&quot;: entry_points},\n\n)</code></pre></div>\n<h1>üï∂ See it in action</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--RiG3kZsy--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_66%2Cw_880/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/4zrhvj5yjzyk63np91g9.gif\"><img src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/practicaldev/image/fetch/s--RiG3kZsy--/c_limit%2Cf_auto%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_66%2Cw_880/https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/4zrhvj5yjzyk63np91g9.gif\" alt=\"See it in action\" title=\"See it in action\"></a></p>\n<h1>üì¢ Discuss</h1>\n<p>What do You wish more python libraries included in their cli?  <a href=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=@_waylonwalker%20More%20libraries%20should%20...%0A%0Awaylonwalker.com/b/scli\">Tweet it @_waylonwalker</a> </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=@_waylonwalker%20More%20libraries%20should%20...%0A%0Awaylonwalker.com/b/scli\" alt=\"Tweet it @_waylonwalker\"></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2020-01-29T06:00:00.000Z","devto_url":null,"devto_id":null,"title":"simple click","description":"Add helpful cli to your python libraries... All of them!","path":"simple_click","twitter_cover":{"id":"b09ed7fe-cda2-5433-99e9-ef1acef98b71","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/2020-02-02 09-40-45_Start.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"6ebb6eff-f788-5974-bb47-b0bb1af85374","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":726,"height":379,"src":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/721a8/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png","srcSet":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/721a8/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png 1x"}}},"cover":{"id":"b09ed7fe-cda2-5433-99e9-ef1acef98b71","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/static/2020-02-02 09-40-45_Start.png","childImageSharp":{"id":"6ebb6eff-f788-5974-bb47-b0bb1af85374","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":726,"height":305,"src":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/9cf71/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png","srcSet":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/9cf71/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png 1x"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":2.380952380952381,"src":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/9cf71/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png","srcSet":"/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/2d6f8/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png 250w,\n/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/03ac3/2020-02-02%2009-40-45_Start.png 500w,\n/static/2b32812f00057bb93fc5d0c8f4e19525/9cf71/2020-